  "prompt": "Which is best Bollywood movie?",
  "response": "It's difficult to definitively say which Bollywood movie is the best, as this is subjective and depends on individual tastes and preferences. However, some highly acclaimed Bollywood films that are often considered among the best include:\n\n1. **Sholay (1975)** - Directed by Ramesh Sippy, this epic action-adventure film is a classic and has had a lasting impact on Indian cinema.\n2. **Pather Panchali (1955)** - Directed by Satyajit Ray, this is the first film in the Apu Trilogy and is revered internationally.\n3. **Dangal (2016)** - Directed by Nitesh Tiwari, this biographical sports drama tells the compelling story of the Phogat family.\n4. **Mother India (1957)** - Directed by Mehboob Khan, this epic drama is iconic and portrays the story of an impoverished woman who struggles to support her family.\n5. **Lagaan (2001)** - Directed by Ashutosh Gowariker, this epic sports drama was India's entry to the Oscars and is celebrated both domestically and internationally.\n6. **Mughal-E-Azam (1960)** - Directed by K. Asif, this historical epic is one of the grandest productions ever made in Indian cinema.\n7. **3 Idiots (2009)** - Directed by Rajkumar Hirani, this coming-of-age comedy-drama has been hugely popular and influential.\n\nThese movies have various attributes that make them standout\u2014storytelling, direction, performances, music, and social impact. Ultimately, the \"best\" movie can vary greatly according to personal tastes and what one values in cinematic experiences.",
